trend_summary: Across the images the peninsula remains chiefly rural. A modest coastal town expands slightly, new roads knit scattered settlements, and additional farm parcels replace forest patches. Minor shoreline change and small-scale reforestation occur, but no large urban cores emerge; built-up footprint stays sparse overall.
notable_changes: Gradual outward growth of the main coastal settlement in the northwest.
New agricultural fields carved from interior woodland, especially mid-peninsula.
Expansion and straightening of the road network linking scattered hamlets.
Localized coastal erosion/accretion altering the northern shoreline ribbon.
Patches of young regrowth forest visible at the southern tip.
